      "writtenOn": "2020-12-21T05:31:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "libsqlite is already a VNDK. That does not mean it must have a stable API for apps, but means that the ABI of the libsqlite.so will be frozen by the Android release process.\nIt does not need to be backward compatible, but must have a stable ABI just inside an Android release.\nAs libsqlite is already a VNDK, we have frozen the ABIs of libsqlite for every Android release since Android P. This CL does not change the current API/ABI policy for libsqlite.\n\nThe CL is to allow the binaries installed in the product partition to use the libsqlite.so. It does not require any additional policies of stable interfaces.",
      "parentUuid": "3ffdc6df_664b3aba",
